<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 9: LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTER AND
        COOLER - OIL FILTER AND HEADER - LEAKAGE TEST
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="inspect" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LEAKAGE TEST</title>
        <para>Inspect oil cooler assembly for leaks using an "Air Pressure" test as follows: Refer to
            <emph type="bold">Figure
                <hotlnk document="e160_241.xml" xrefid="ef1600920">9.20</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            .
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Fasten oil cooler leakage test plate to oil cooler headers using new oil cooler gaskets.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil filter.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install air pressure gauge to oil cooler filter header at turbocharger supply fitting
                location.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Immerse assembly in a container of clean "tap" water.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Apply 690 kPa (100 psi) air pressure while immersed.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect header castings, O-Ring seals and 1/4NPTF water side opening for moving or growing
                bubbles. Replace components as required.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
